paragraph.content:
the charge shall be entered by the master in the official log book and shall be
                read to the seafarer by the master, who shall record therein that it has been so
                read;

the evidence of any witness called by the master shall be heard in the presence
                of the seafarer, who shall be afforded reasonable opportunity to question the
                witness on his evidence;

the seafarer shall be permitted to call witnesses to give evidence on his
                behalf, and any such witness may be questioned by the master on his
                evidence;
